name: Daylight savings time
summary: Daylight saving time, the seasonal practice of advancing clocks by one hour in the spring and reverting them an hour in the fall, is scheduled to end on November 3, 2024. This means that on the first Sunday of November, clocks will "fall back" by one hour, giving people an extra hour of sleep. The end of daylight saving time is a reminder to adjust clocks, smoke detectors, and carbon monoxide detectors. It also serves as an opportunity to reflect on the pros and cons of daylight saving time, with some research suggesting it can have negative impacts on health and well-being.

name: Jayden Daniels
summary: Washington Commanders' quarterback Jayden Daniels is facing uncertainty for Sunday's game against the Chicago Bears due to a rib injury. Daniel's status remains unclear, and he has been ruled a game-time decision. He returned to practice but missed Wednesday's session because of the injury and is listed as questionable. The extent of his injury is being described as "week-to-week," indicating ongoing uncertainty about his availability in the coming weeks. Daniels' absence would have a significant impact on the Commanders' offense, as he has been their starting quarterback since Week 4. His injury also coincides with potential losses within the Bears' passing unit, adding to the uncertainty surrounding both teams' offensive performances this weekend.
